SNP leader Nicola Sturgeon refused to rule out demanding a re-run referendum before 2020 . 
  She insisted last year's vote was a once-in-a-generation chance to decide on the future of the Union . 
  But she left open the possibility of a referendum in a future SNP manifesto . 
  Labour leader Willie Rennie said she had 'broken a promise the size of Ben Nevis' on another referendum . 
 